This paper deals with Spatial Voting Theory, which is a subfield of Game Theory (cs.GT). It also involves modeling and analyzing elections, which can be categorized under Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the concept of expected distortion, which is related to Social Choice Theory (cs.SI).
